<h1 id="addition">Addition</h1>
<p>Addition is hard, right? Nope, but itâ€™s even easier for our computers!</p>

<h2 id="implementation-details">Implementation Details</h2>
<ul>
  <li data-marker="*">Write a program that adds 2 numbers.</li>
  <li data-marker="*">You can use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">get_int()</code> to grab an integer.</li>
  <li data-marker="*">Store those values in variables of type <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">int</code></li>
  <li data-marker="*">Print the total of those values out.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="hints">Hints</h3>
<p>Remember <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">printf</code> formatting codes? You can use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">%i</code> to print out the value of a variable of type <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">int</code>.</p>

<p><strong>Example:</strong> <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">example.c</code></p>
<div class="language-c highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="kt">int</span> <span class="n">number</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">;</span>
<span class="n">printf</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s">"Your magic number is %i</span><span class="se">\n</span><span class="s">"</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">number</span><span class="p">);</span>
</code></pre></div></div>
<p><strong>Output:</strong></p>
<div class="language-console highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="gp">$</span><span class="w"> </span>./example
<span class="go">Your magic number is 5
</span></code></pre></div></div>

